thread.title: Budget 14/15 outcome confirms improvement

title: Budget 14/15 outcome confirms improvement
text:
Mon, Sep 21, 2015, 9:40 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 20 mins. Budget 14/15 outcome confirms improvement AAP – 18 minutes ago Print 
In one of his last acts as treasurer, Joe Hockey has released the final budget outcome for the 2014/15 financial year. 
In a joint statement with Finance Minister Mathias Cormann, they said the budget recorded a deficit of $37.9 billion, which was a $3.3 billion improvement compared with the estimate in the 2015/16 May budget. 
"The improvement in the bottom line was driven by government spending being $2.9 billion lower than expected," they said. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Finance News Update, what you need to know AAP
